1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 18=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:54,710
The door is opening.

4
00:01:46,790 --> 00:01:48,070
We shouldn't die here.

5
00:01:53,870 --> 00:01:54,920
Let me out.

6
00:01:55,189 --> 00:01:56,595
- Oh, my.
- Let me catch my breath.

7
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:58,400
I'm about to suffocate.

8
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:01,510
I'm about to suffocate.

9
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,200
What did you just play?

10
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,590
I just played a random tune.

11
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,910
Ms. He, I'm not criticizing you.

12
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:10,680
You should've acted sooner.

13
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,680
You let Lu mess around for so long.

14
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,960
I was almost suffocated.

15
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,240
I just thought of it.

16
00:02:16,150 --> 00:02:17,190
What a surprise.

17
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:20,240
Ms. He even knows
The Phoenix Seeks a Mate.

18
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,840
I shouldn't have shown off.

19
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:26,360
Who did she seek to release us?

20
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,030
Nonsense.

21
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:31,150
The Phoenix Seeks a Mate

22
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:34,560
is a song Sima Xiangru wrote
to Zhuo Wenjun,

23
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:37,680
expressing deep love.

24
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:42,030
Expressing love?

25
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:48,030
Didn't you see Ms. He

26
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,560
keep looking

27
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,400
at Chen Youxi?

28
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:55,960
- Why?
- I think you should

29
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,280
bring your wife to scout out.

30
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,400
Whose wife?

31
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,400
- Hurry.
- Nothing happened.

32
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:07,750
Miss Bai, do you know

33
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,150
that ancient tune expresses love?

34
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:11,150
You two can talk slowly.

35
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,030
- I'll learn it for you.
- Take your time.

36
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:16,560
It was for Zhuo Wenjun.

37
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:18,840
- I...
- You...

38
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:21,750
You go first.

39
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:25,000
Do you know why I thought of that tune?

40
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,150
Why?

41
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,080
Look, on this chime bell,

42
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:30,560
there are many phoenixes.

43
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:32,840
Also, when we entered the tomb,

44
00:03:33,330 --> 00:03:34,180
there were

45
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,590
many phoenix patterns inside.

46
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,030
I think the tomb builder

47
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:40,750
was probably the princess's admirer.

48
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,470
So,

49
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:45,150
that tune fits the theme best.

50
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,960
You really never heard it before?

51
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:50,080
It's my first time.

52
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:27,110
Shutong!

53
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:43,110
Chubby.

54
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:45,240
What's wrong with Ms. He?

55
00:04:48,070 --> 00:04:49,390
Was she poisoned?

56
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:51,270
By mercury?

57
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,160
I don't think so.

58
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,390
Everyone else is fine.

59
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:06,360
Don't you have candy?

60
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,790
Candy.

61
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,270
What's wrong with Ms. He?

62
00:05:13,510 --> 00:05:14,350
Nothing.

63
00:05:14,830 --> 00:05:16,920
She's been active all day
without eating.

64
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:18,480
It's probably low blood sugar.

65
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,160
Hold her.

66
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,750
Hungry?

67
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,270
No.

68
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:48,070
Perhaps you're not hungry physically,

69
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:49,830
but your spirit can't be lacking.

70
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:51,360
Here, have this.

71
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,200
This...

72
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,240
You don't want to hear it?

73
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,400
I'll sing for you.

74
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:08,830
♪In a distant land, there's a girl♪

75
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,480
♪Her name is Yelia♪

76
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:15,120
No, let's listen together.

77
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,026
Let's listen together.

78
00:06:17,950 --> 00:06:18,790
Go.

79
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:24,390
♪In a distant land, there's a girl♪

80
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,120
♪Her name is Yelia♪

81
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:41,160
♪In the far night sky♪

82
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:44,610
♪There's the brightest star♪

83
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:49,500
♪Legend says it belongs to Yelia♪

84
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:53,090
♪It's her charming eyes♪

85
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:58,060
♪Searching the vast galaxy♪

86
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:01,660
♪No matter how thick the clouds♪

87
00:07:02,650 --> 00:07:06,570
♪Every night, look up♪

88
00:07:06,790 --> 00:07:10,560
♪Until the moon sets
and the sky brightens♪

89
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:14,290
♪Her long hair flows in the wind♪

90
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:18,230
♪Her skirt sways lightly♪

91
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:22,440
♪The moon loses its glow♪

92
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:27,290
♪The stars dim because of you♪

93
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:30,930
♪Even if the legend is forgotten♪

94
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:35,350
♪And fairy tales are sealed in dust♪

95
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:39,160
♪Walking hand in hand with you♪

96
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:42,510
♪The heart still trembles♪

97
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:48,190
♪Yelia, the mysterious Yelia♪

98
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:54,800
♪I have already found her♪

99
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,760
How was it?

100
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,355
Was it better on the tape

101
00:08:03,366 --> 00:08:04,310
or my singing?

102
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,560
How long are they going to rest?

103
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,000
I just let you relax.

104
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,240
Why are you tense again?

105
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,560
That must be uncomfortable.

106
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:13,600
I don't have time
to waste here with you.

107
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:19,000
You have a sharp tongue
but a soft heart.

108
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,310
Good kid.

109
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:22,190
I think you just talk too much.

110
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,000
Enough.

111
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,070
I'll ask when we depart.

112
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,480
Not awake yet?

113
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,870
Let her sleep a bit more.

114
00:08:41,510 --> 00:08:43,360
How affectionate.

115
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,030
I just played Yelia

116
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:48,000
for Bai Lingling.

117
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,600
Do you know where the inspiration
came from?

118
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,910
No idea?

119
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,790
Ms. He.

120
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,150
Lower your voice.

121
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,080
You've been holding her for a while.

122
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,390
Don't you wonder

123
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:04,910
why she played The Phoenix Seeks a Mate

124
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:06,870
at such a dangerous moment?

125
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:12,440
She's asleep and can't hear it.

126
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,480
I have to tell you.

127
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:16,150
Think about it.

128
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,600
What's the meaning of that tune?

129
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,390
Maybe some words

130
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:22,080
need us men to say first.

131
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,600
Learn from me.

132
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,000
You're awake?

133
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,600
What? What sound?

134
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:37,030
Probably Huang Long again.

135
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,280
Impossible.

136
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,870
We stole all his explosives.

137
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,560
Yes.

138
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,790
I took all of his explosives.

139
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,510
Ms. He, you're awake.

140
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,630
You don't know. When you fainted,

141
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:50,360
Chen Youxi was panicking,

142
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,030
mouth skewed, foaming.

143
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,560
Enough.

144
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,320
What's wrong with me?

145
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,080
Probably low blood sugar.

146
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,080
Here, have a candy.

147
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,360
I can't watch this. Too sweet.

148
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,670
Carry these pieces with you.

149
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:04,720
Though the explosives
in the bags were stolen,

150
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,550
they still carried many with them.

151
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,080
So,

152
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,480
they'll keep blowing things up?

153
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:11,440
I hope not.

154
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:13,000
If they're careless,

155
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,320
they could blow up the main hall.

156
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,480
Then where would we cry?

157
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,630
You three go ahead.

158
00:10:16,836 --> 00:10:18,076
I'll stay with her for a while.

159
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,200
Fine.

160
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,200
It's fine.

161
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,600
I'm better; let's go together.

162
00:10:21,630 --> 00:10:22,983
Lu, don't forget the water bottle.

163
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:39,910
Why didn't you warn me

164
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:41,150
about Huang Long?

165
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,390
I could've covered for you.

166
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:44,240
Lu, seeing you busy,

167
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,720
kept doubting you.

168
00:10:45,843 --> 00:10:47,312
I said it, but you didn't believe me.

169
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:48,630
They may not,

170
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:50,440
but I do.

171
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,510
How could I not trust you?

172
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,200
How strange.

173
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,670
We've been here before.

174
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:06,000
Why are we back here again?

175
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:08,320
When did you come here?

176
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,240
Where is this?

177
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,790
Didn't I tell you?

178
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,670
When we first arrived,

179
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:14,052
you two were in the secret passage;

180
00:11:14,063 --> 00:11:15,030
we were wandering above.

181
00:11:15,030 --> 00:11:16,080
There was a big face.

182
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,360
It appeared with light

183
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,960
and disappeared without it.

184
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,080
The big face?

185
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:20,920
Strange.

186
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:23,670
Why are we back?

187
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,480
Lu, light the candle.

188
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,320
Sure.

189
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,160
Look.

190
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,480
There really is a big face.

191
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:45,360
Could it be that this tomb

192
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:47,480
has two identical chambers?

193
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,440
Look.

194
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,480
This small Ding.

195
00:11:52,790 --> 00:11:53,960
I was playing with it here.

196
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:54,800
Then I put it here.

197
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,040
Look.

198
00:11:56,596 --> 00:11:58,899
These are the bullet holes left
when I stopped Huang Long

199
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,000
from shooting.

200
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:01,120
It's here.

201
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:03,910
This must be it.

202
00:12:03,910 --> 00:12:05,720
Look at the entrance, this lamp,

203
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:07,000
and these furnishings,

204
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,150
including these two little lions
guarding here.

205
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:14,360
Where are the lions?

206
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,329
How did they turn into a tomb passage?

207
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,720
The lions here are gone too.

208
00:12:19,696 --> 00:12:21,042
And there's an extra tomb passage.

209
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:29,080
Could this be the legendary nether tomb?

210
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,200
It just changes into whatever it wants?

211
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,150
Don't talk nonsense.

212
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:34,960
Then how do you explain

213
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,030
that these entrances and passages

214
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,960
can appear and disappear at will?

215
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,560
Listen.

216
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,690
Let's split into two groups
for the two passages

217
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,680
and meet here later

218
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,173
to share the information we collect.

219
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,120
Okay, Commander Chen.

220
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,960
How about this?

221
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:51,150
You two take that passage.

222
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,030
I'll take Miss Bai down this one.

223
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:54,150
I want to go that way.

224
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:56,710
You...

225
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:58,910
Fine, Chen, you go this way.

226
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:29,390
♪In a distant land, there's a girl♪

227
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:30,240
♪Her name is Yelia♪

228
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,080
What's wrong?

229
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,560
Nothing.

230
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,840
Just tired. Singing a song to relax.

231
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,630
It's rare to be alone with me.

232
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,360
Don't you have anything to say?

233
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:42,840
Together?

234
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,960
Didn't I force you here?

235
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,440
If I hadn't,

236
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,150
you would've gone with Chen Youxi.

237
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,550
Are you jealous?

238
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:58,670
This is nothing special.

239
00:13:58,670 --> 00:13:59,960
Why would I be jealous?

240
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,440
What a pure young man.

241
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:15,920
Miss Bai.

242
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:16,910
Well.

243
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:18,670
You flatter me.

244
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:20,030
I've been through a lot.

245
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:21,150
Once we're out of this tomb,

246
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:22,510
follow me home.

247
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:24,030
We're colleagues. Won't you get bored?

248
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:25,600
How could I be?

249
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,030
Colleagues share language and topics.

250
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:29,010
Right?

251
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,840
Think about it.
If we weren't colleagues,

252
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,240
what could we even talk about?

253
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:33,480
Look here.

254
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,150
Another eyeball.

255
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,720
Don't you find it familiar?

256
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:51,320
Yeah.

257
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:52,966
Chen Youxi has one on his back.

258
00:14:52,977 --> 00:14:53,960
Of course, it's familiar.

259
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,670
No, this pattern

260
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:57,510
and the one at the bottom
of Huang Long's box

261
00:14:57,670 --> 00:14:58,870
are exactly the same

262
00:14:58,870 --> 00:14:59,870
in size and shape.

263
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,200
One is concave; one is convex.

264
00:15:02,550 --> 00:15:03,480
There must be

265
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:04,870
a connection between them.

266
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:05,840
You mean

267
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:08,200
these two eyeball patterns

268
00:15:08,790 --> 00:15:10,630
might be the mechanism to open the door?

269
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:12,590
What?

270
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,000
We're going to find Huang Long?

271
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,080
Your passage is a dead end, right?

272
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,360
So?

273
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,790
We don't know what's behind that door.

274
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:21,630
Right?

275
00:15:22,550 --> 00:15:24,910
We can't risk our lives

276
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,000
for something unknown and uncertain.

277
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:30,080
Lu, I don't agree with you.

278
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,270
We've always risked

279
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:33,080
for uncertain things.

280
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,320
Do you see it clearly?

281
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:36,840
Could it be Bai Ling's trick,

282
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:38,320
wanting us to walk into a trap?

283
00:15:38,670 --> 00:15:40,550
No, Ms. He.

284
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,360
I think you're overthinking.

285
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:45,030
Now, she's on the same boat with us.

286
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,510
I'm not on the same boat with her.

287
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,790
My goal is simple:

288
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,120
Open the door and move forward.

289
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,240
